<h1 class="title">What accounts for the wild success of our evolved intelligence ?</h1>
<p>
Why should our intelligence, which evolved to be good at hunting or
attracting mates, lead to the phenomenal success in understanding the
deepest laws of physics.
</p>

<p>
Not only is the universe (apparently) fine-tuned for our existence,
but our consciousness is intelligent is enough to discover this fine-tuning.
</p>

<p>
Deutsch Argument about the unlimited scope of intelligence <a href="BeginningOfInfinity.html#ID-79681BB2-0968-4644-8EA5-905DB31B28AD">BeginningOfInfinity</a>
Anything that is not super natural must have explainations discoverable by general intelligence.
